seem to be any gusto in this office due to the lack of leadership and disorganization by the front office they claim to mail things to you address when nothing is received they claim to call you for appointments  even going as far as to say that i spoke to you on x day when that never happened and then they have fees for everything even if you want a copy of your test results the behavior of the office support staff has worsened over the years which is why i have found another practice  that is just as knowledgeable as dr stewart and amanda minus the rude front office team do you value your time dr stewarts office wont ive been to dr stewarts office twice now oct   may  both times i have gone for a routine visit i have had to wait waaaaaaay too long this past visit may  i arrived at  for an  appointment i was perfectly fine to wait  minutes until my appointment i was the only one in the waiting room the entire time i was there at  i was called back to take my vitals record my weight and explain my symptoms after those quick checks i was walked down the hall to an exam room and put in there by myself to wait to see someone and thennothing an hour went by before i finally just got up and walked out i told the receptionist that i could no longer wait to see a physician based on my schedule i needed to see a physician but i didnt need for it to be an event requiring me to take a halfday off of work to see them after leaving i fully expected one of james stewarts staff to call me perhaps apologetically and attempt to reschedule needless to say they never called hows that for customer service find someone else i can assure you that your appointment time doesnt really matter to them i saw the reviews dr stewarts office got on this website prior to my appt however his office is very close to my house so i decided to try it out for myself i was quite surprised i found his staff very friendly the nurse practitioner i saw was very knowledgeable and took her time with me i felt like they really cared about my well being i loved the receptionist i found her nice and pleasant with everyone even the girls in the back that took my blood were very nice i was very impressed in fact im moving my husband and daughters over to this practice even going to move my  yr old parents i went in with very low expectations and walked out feeling great i would highly recommend this office to anyone this review is more for dr stewarts staff than for him i am actually a patient of his partner dr mouledous and havent met dr stewart at all but i am acquainted with his staff nurse was very nicebut is the only nurse i have ever met that couldnt find a vein in my arm i left with a very painful bruise receptionist just rubs me the wrong way and doesnt seem to have any organizational skills she had me scheduled for the wrong doctor but thats ok you can just come back on friday please have a little more respect for my time stewart james l md unclaimed this business has not yet been claimed by the owner or a representative claim this business to view business statistics receive messages from prospective customers and respond to reviews  reviews details  opens a popup rating details internal medicine edit  opens a popup edit category write a review add photo share  opens a popup bookmark  opens a popup get directions swap startend points start from start from swap startend points stewart james l md  old alabama rd alpharetta ga  get directions edit  old alabama rdalpharetta ga  get directions phone number   send to your phone health  medical doctors internal medicine add photos ad the joint chiropractic alpharetta at windward plaza  reviews  miles away from stewart james l md aymara m said i dont normally write reviews but i felt that the team at the joint chiropractic needed to be recognized dr jarry and dee are awesome i immediately felt welcomed upon arriving dee came around the… read more in chiropractors ad intown primary care  reviews  miles away from stewart jam