s the staff i have had no issues the staff was always easy to work with to reschedule appointments which is usually where office staff tend to be rude i really enjoy having amanda as my doctor im in good health so i havent been a complicated patient but the times i have been sick and needed an appointment quickly it was easy to schedule and get the attention i needed amanda is extremely thorough and has a great memory she always asks me about something i mentioned to her a year ago at my last visit she knows her patients well which in my opinion is one of the most important qualities in a doctor she notes events in my life and treats health in the same way following up on any concerns or conditions i had mentioned in the past i highly recommend this office for a longterm doctor that will know your history and provide genuine care its tough to give any business a low review and sadly this review would have been much higher had it not been for the terrible front office staff the nurse practitioner amanda choi and dr stewart are great both are personable and knowledgeable and i think amanda is very through and has a great memory however when it comes to the office the buck stops here ann the front office person is curt rude and it feels like youre pulling teeth to get anything out of her her tone is always snide on the phone and you can tell that she is dispassionate about being in customer service the office manager just hides behind ann and there doesnt seem to be any gusto in this office due to the lack of leadership and disorganization by the front office they claim to mail things to you address when nothing is received they claim to call you for appointments  even going as far as to say that i spoke to you on x day when that never happened and then they have fees for everything even if you want a copy of your test results the behavior of the office support staff has worsened over the years which is why i have found another practice  that is just as knowledgeable a